                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 46</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Cabaldon<br/>(Coauthors: Senators Allen, Alvarado-Gil, Arreguín, Ashby, Becker, Blakespear, Caballero, Cervantes, Cortese, Durazo, Grayson, Hurtado, Laird, Limón, McNerney, Menjivar, Padilla, Pérez, Reyes, Richardson, Rubio, Umberg, Wahab, Weber Pierson, and Wiener)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>May 19, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Affordable Housing Month. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SR 46, Cabaldon.
                          </span></div><div><span id="digesttext"/></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_2ACD295B-C308-4505-BBCB-E161CB219303"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Access to quality, affordable housing is fundamental to creating healthy, safe, and sustainable communities in the State of California, supporting the California dream; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E10580AE-E96F-4C75-A64E-D32E50320B97"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Rising housing costs have displaced longtime residents, forced families into overcrowded conditions, and contributed to homelessness, threatening the racial and economic diversity of the State of California; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_975A748E-9427-480A-BD14-DD5112CB95FD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Affordable housing with wraparound services is a key solution to homelessness and is essential to the well-being of seniors, families, youth, veterans, and individuals with disabilities or special needs in the State of California; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_006A7CD8-8433-44C8-B637-54CCFCB4DE3C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, It is necessary for the State of California to allocate the resources necessary to produce and preserve affordable housing, including an affordable housing bond; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_DBFE523E-3898-46D4-8FAA-DC27EFC9BA4E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Affordable housing organizations recognize May as Affordable Housing Month, underscoring the urgent need for action by the state to address the growing housing crisis; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E5436F5D-0EB6-4F73-9D1E-2FBF6373DADF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, That the Senate proclaims May 2025 as Affordable Housing Month and affirms its commitment to supporting affordable housing solutions to preserve the California dream; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_5E6B6794-3B2E-49E2-AA8A-8DAE4C31F806"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
